[size=14pt][b][color=#FF00FF]POST-QUANTUM CRYPTOGRAPHY STACK[/color][/b][/size]

Q-NarwhalKnight runs the most advanced post-quantum cryptography stack in production:

[list]
[li][b]SQIsign Signatures[/b] - Isogeny-based post-quantum signatures (smallest PQ signatures available)[/li]
[li][b]AEGIS-QL Access Control[/b] - Sparse Ring-LWE encryption, 50%+ faster than Kyber-768[/li]
[li][b]Quantum Mixer[/b] - ZK-STARK proofs for complete transaction privacy[/li]
[li][b]Genus-2 Jacobian VDF[/b] - Verifiable delay function for ASIC-resistant mining[/li]
[li][b]Tor Integration[/b] - Network-level anonymity with dedicated circuits[/li]
[li][b]Kyber1024 Key Encapsulation[/b] - Quantum-safe key exchange for P2P encryption[/li]
[/list]

[b]Why SQIsign over Dilithium?[/b]
[code]Dilithium5: 4,595 bytes signature size
SQIsign:    177 bytes signature size (26x smaller!)

At 48,000+ TPS, this saves:
- 212 MB/s of bandwidth
- Faster block propagation
- Lower storage requirements[/code]

